  "texts": [
    "The 3D-printed PLA substrate, produced by fused deposition modeling (FDM), features circular arc-shaped ridges with a peak-to-peak spacing of 154 µm.",
    "The PLA substrate is hydrophilic, with an equilibrium contact angle of θ eq,p = 76 • in the parallel direction and θ eq,t = 63 • in the transversal direction [24].",
    "The water droplets impacted the PLA surface at significantly lower velocities of U 0 = 0.",
    "We use data from the 3D direct numerical simulations conducted by Fink et al. [29] within the framework of the phasefield method [14,41] implemented in the open-source computational fluid dynamics (CFD) software OpenFOAM ® [91], for the training and validation of the developed PINNs.",
    "These simulations featured droplet impingement on flat and structured hydrophobic Polydimethylsiloxane (PDMS) substrates."
